I'm using this particular version because I get the best results from it, but the difference is minor, I'm sure you can use whatever Wan 2.1 lightx2v version

The rest of the models are just the normal Wan 2.1 bunch. Nothing special.

nodes.title: Mark what you want removed
widgets_values: Put a few green points on the thing you want removed, and some red points around but outside the thing you want removed.

nodes.title: Notes
widgets_values:
Results may vary depending on what you want to remove. I'm removing logos in a smallish video so it was easy. Even then, it was not perfect, there was this slight perturbance where the logos used to be.

I have a 24 G VRAM card, and I had to break the video up into 297 frame chunks. I chose that number because it took about 500s each and there was no threat of OOM.

Your framecount needs to be 4n+1. just like normal Wan. The video dimensions also adhere to normal Wan 2.1 restraints, the width and height need to be divisble by 16. The resize is automatic to aim for the 480p which is Wan 2.1 standard, which is about 0.42 Megapixels. If you're aiming for 720p, adjust to 0.9 Megapixels. (You'll probably OOM though)

Good luck, this is not an official release.
